                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1105">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/16664.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Governor of Texas</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin, Texas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-02T12:15:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 2, 1915—12.15 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Replying to your favor October 30 beg to advise that you will receive my hearty
                    cooperation along the lines suggested for quieting border conditions. Have given
                    your telegram widespread advertisement and have asked the cooperation of
                    everybody in carrying out the policy suggested by you.</p>
                <p>Thanking you [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. E. Ferguson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
